               <msContents>
                  <summary>The damage to the papyrus and the resulting damage to the text prevents a certain conclusion regarding the content of this text. From line 2 (salutem) It is clear that the text had the form of a letter, but other words make it clear that this was hardly a private letter. This text may therefore be an official letter, which may be concerned with legionnary veterans (lines 4 and 9). In that case, this text can only be a copy emanating from a perhaps military office of significant rank.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Location: Ann Arbor</note>
                     <note type="general">Pub. status: Recto; Verso contains a Greek transaction concerning land in the first half of the third century A.D.</note>
                     <note type="lines">1-10</note>
                     <note type="paleography">Written in a semicursive with a rather strong rightward slant. Letters often detached. Written in brown ink.</note>
